{
  "doc_id": "39295",
  "text": "In clinical practice, dofetilide is used in the pharmacological management and treatment of atrial fibrillation (AF). Dofetilide is efficient in conversion to sinus rhythm, and maintenance of sinus rhythm, but has some restrictions [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Dofetilide can also be used as adjunctive therapy in patients with life-threatening ventricular arrhythmias who have an implantable cardioverter-defibrillator (reviewed in [CITATION_3] ). Despite the potential for inducing torsades de pointes, with the correct dosing, adjusted for renal function and QT, this risk remains low. The DIAMOND trial documented no excess mortality in patients at risk with coronary artery disease and heart failure [CITATION_4] and actually improved survival in patients who were successfully converted to sinus rhythm [CITATION_5] .",
